Frontend Deployment using Amazon S3 (Static Website Hosting)
📌 Overview

In this step, we will:

Create an S3 bucket
Enable static website hosting
Upload chatbot frontend (index.html)
Connect frontend with API Gateway
Make the website publicly accessible


🪜 Step 1 — Create S3 Bucket
Open AWS Management Console
Navigate to Amazon S3
Click Create bucket
Configure Bucket:
Bucket type → General purpose

Bucket name →

bedrock-agent-chat-ui

(or any unique name)

⚠️ Important:

Uncheck:

Block all public access
Tick acknowledgment checkbox
Click Create bucket


🌐 Step 2 — Enable Static Website Hosting
Open your created bucket
Go to Properties tab
Scroll to Static website hosting
Click Edit
Configure:
Enable → ✅
Hosting type → Host a static website

Index document:

index.html
Click Save
📌 Output:

S3 will generate a website URL like:

http://ritik-bedrock-agent-chat-ui.s3-website.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com

💻 Step 3 — Create & Configure Frontend (index.html)

🔹 3.1 Get Frontend Code

Open s3-web-code-file 

🔹 3.2 Create File Locally
Open VS Code / Notepad
Create new file
Save as:
index.html

⚠️ Make sure:

NOT index.html.txt
Extension must be .html

🔹 3.3 Paste Code
Copy full code from s3-web-code-file Paste into index.html
Save file

🔹 3.4 Update API URL (VERY IMPORTANT)

Find this line:

const API_URL = "YOUR_API_GATEWAY_URL";

Replace with your API:

const API_URL = "https://9780b0dyo5.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/chat";
⚠️ Important:
/chat must be included
Same endpoint used in Postman


📤 Step 4 — Upload Frontend to S3
Open your S3 bucket
Click Upload

Select file:

index.html
Click Upload


🔓 Step 5 — Allow Public Access (Bucket Policy)
Go to Permissions tab
Scroll to Bucket Policy
Click Edit
Paste this policy:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::bedrock-agent-chat-ui/*"
    }
  ]
}

👉 Replace:

bedrock-agent-chat-ui → your bucket name
Click Save changes


🌍 Step 6 — Access Your Website

Open:

http://ritik-bedrock-agent-chat-ui.s3-website.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com


✅ Final Architecture Flow
User (Browser)
   ↓
S3 Static Website (Frontend UI)
   ↓
API Gateway (/chat)
   ↓
Lambda (Chat Proxy)
   ↓
Bedrock Agent
   ↓
AWS Services (EIP, EBS, etc.)


🎉 Result
Fully working AI chatbot UI
Secure backend using Lambda
AI-powered AWS automation system
